productParameters.detailedDescription:
The ‘bank  Home Loan Variable’ is a variable rate loan that is full of features and it gives you the flexibility to react to the changes in your life or circumstances.

Benefits such as:
• the ability to make extra repayments, and
• no early repayment costs if you decide to sell your property

A variable rate loan means that the interest rate that is applied to your home loan can change, for example, due to changes in the economy. This means your repayments decrease when interest rates go down, and your repayments will increase when interest rates go up.

features.additionalInfo: bank  Redraw could let you access extra payments you've made to an eligible loan when you need to

An offset account is a transaction account linked to an eligible home loan. The money you have in this account could offset the amount you owe on that loan, and you'll only be charged the interest on the difference
Available to customers refinancing an eligible non-bank home loan that is greater than $250,000 for applications submitted before 30 September 2024. T&Cs apply.
